    "Tianhao Shen Ge Zhang Yuhang Wu Cong Liu Ziya Zhou Ziyang Ma Liumeng Xue Ziyu Wang Qin Liu Tianyu Zheng Yizhi Li Yinghao Ma Yiming Liang Xiaowei Chi Ruibo Liu Zili Wang Pengfei Li Jingcheng Wu Advisors Chenghua Lin Qifeng Liu Tao Jiang Wenhao Huang Wenhu Chen Emmanouil Benetos Jie Fu Gus Xia Roger Dannenberg Correspondence Wei Xue, weixue@ust.hk Shiyin Kang, shiyin.kang@kunlun-inc.com Yike Guo, yikeguo@ust.hk A Introduction to ABC Notation ABC notation is a text-based system for music notation, particularly popular for notating folk and traditional tunes.",
    "It was designed to be easily read by humans and to be simple to type without special musical fonts or software.",
    "It offers unique advantages when interfacing with deep learning models: • Data Efficiency: ABC notation compactly represents musical information in a text format, making it highly efficient in terms of storage and transmission.",
    "This compactness is advantageous when training deep learning models as it minimizes data overhead.",
    "• Easy Preprocessing: Being a structured text format, ABC notation can be easily tokenized and converted into numerical sequences or embeddings, a crucial step in preparing data for neural networks."
  ],
